<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,320,635]" pageId="8" pageNumber="171">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,276,321,347]" pageId="8" pageNumber="171">Taxonomy</emphasis>
. The senior author has examined the 
<typeStatus box="[697,795,320,346]" pageId="8" pageNumber="171">holotype</typeStatus>
and a 
<typeStatus box="[869,965,321,347]" pageId="8" pageNumber="171">paratype</typeStatus>
(NHML), and specimens in RAB. 
<bibRefCitation author="Schedl, K. E." pageId="8" pageNumber="171" pagination="117 - 124" refId="ref6549" refString="Schedl, K. E. (1980) Zur Synonymie der Borkenkafer. XXVIII. Zeitschrift der Arbeitsgemeinschaft Osterreichischer Entomologen, 31 (1979), 117 - 124." type="journal article" year="1980">Schedl (1980)</bibRefCitation>
considered that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schedl" authorityYear="1975" box="[408,652,356,382]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Xyleborus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="171" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="granulosus">
<emphasis box="[408,652,356,382]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="171">Xyleborus granulosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was a synonym of this species, but the two species were distinguished by 
<bibRefCitation author="Beaver, R. A." box="[186,351,393,419]" pageId="8" pageNumber="171" pagination="87 - 97" refId="ref5359" refString="Beaver, R. A. (1991) New synonymy and taxonomic changes in Pacific Scolytidae (Coleoptera). Annalen des Naturhistorisches Museum, Wien, 92 B, 87 - 97." type="journal article" year="1991">Beaver (1991)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="171" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,320,635]" pageId="8" pageNumber="171">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,428,454]" pageId="8" pageNumber="171">Distribution.</emphasis>
The species is endemic to 
<collectingCountry box="[655,697,428,454]" name="Fiji" pageId="8" pageNumber="171">Fiji</collectingCountry>
, where it occurs in both high and low altitude rain forest (
<bibRefCitation author="Roberts, H." pageId="8" pageNumber="171" pagination="251 - 272" refId="ref6423" refString="Roberts, H. (1977) Observations on the biology of some tropical rain forest Scolytidae (Coleoptera) from Fiji. II. Subfamily Ipinae - tribe Xyleborini. Journal of Natural History, 11, 251 - 272. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222937700770181" type="journal article" year="1977">Roberts 1977</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="171" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,320,635]" pageId="8" pageNumber="171">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,295,500,526]" pageId="8" pageNumber="171">Biology.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Roberts, H." box="[302,471,500,527]" pageId="8" pageNumber="171" pagination="251 - 272" refId="ref6423" refString="Roberts, H. (1977) Observations on the biology of some tropical rain forest Scolytidae (Coleoptera) from Fiji. II. Subfamily Ipinae - tribe Xyleborini. Journal of Natural History, 11, 251 - 272. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222937700770181" type="journal article" year="1977">Roberts (1977)</bibRefCitation>
described in detail the gallery system, brood size and development, and noted associated species of ambrosia beetles. He recorded the species from nine different families of host trees (
<bibRefCitation author="Roberts, H." box="[1268,1424,536,563]" pageId="8" pageNumber="171" pagination="251 - 272" refId="ref6423" refString="Roberts, H. (1977) Observations on the biology of some tropical rain forest Scolytidae (Coleoptera) from Fiji. II. Subfamily Ipinae - tribe Xyleborini. Journal of Natural History, 11, 251 - 272. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222937700770181" type="journal article" year="1977">Roberts 1977</bibRefCitation>
). It is evidently polyphagous. In contrast to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Beaver &amp; Petrov &amp; Sittichaya" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Browne" baseAuthorityYear="1974" box="[632,796,572,598]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Melanesicus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="171" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="deformatus">
<emphasis box="[632,796,572,598]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="171">M. deformatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see above), emergence is probably confined to the day, and the species was never taken at light (
<bibRefCitation author="Roberts, H." box="[608,764,608,635]" pageId="8" pageNumber="171" pagination="251 - 272" refId="ref6423" refString="Roberts, H. (1977) Observations on the biology of some tropical rain forest Scolytidae (Coleoptera) from Fiji. II. Subfamily Ipinae - tribe Xyleborini. Journal of Natural History, 11, 251 - 272. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222937700770181" type="journal article" year="1977">Roberts 1977</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
